# IRoad Super Admin Control Panel - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Overview
- Django-based Super Admin Control Panel for IRoad SaaS platform
- PostgreSQL database (no SQLite ever)
- Multi-app structure: one app per module domain
- Designer HTML files are in D:\iroad\designerDesign\IRoad\ — always use these as base for templates, never create new HTML from scratch

## Coding Standards
- Always use Django class-based views (CBV) unless a function view is explicitly requested
- Always use Django forms or ModelForms for all form handling
- Never hardcode credentials — always use environment variables via python-decouple
- All models must have created_at, updated_at auto timestamps
- All models must have created_by, updated_by FK to AdminUser where applicable
- Use UUID as primary key for all models unless doc specifies auto-integer
- All database migrations must be created after every model change
- Never use SQLite — PostgreSQL only

## Template Rules
- **Do not change visual/UI design unless the user explicitly requests it.** Preserve layout, typography, spacing, colors, and designer HTML structure; wire backend (views, forms, URLs, data) without redesigning pages.
- base.html must be the master layout extended by every page
- sidebar.html, navbar.html, footer.html must be separate partials included in base.html
- Every template extends base.html using {% extends 'base.html' %}
- Static files (CSS/JS/images) must be loaded using {% load static %} and {% static %}
- Designer CSS and JS must never be modified — only referenced

## Security Rules
- Never store passwords in plain text
- Always use Django's built-in password hashing
- Login required decorator or LoginRequiredMixin on every view except login page
- CSRF protection must always be enabled (never disable)
- Debug must be False in production settings

## App Structure Rules
- superadmin/ app handles: auth, roles, admin users, dashboard
- Each future module gets its own app
- Never mix module logic across apps
- Always register new apps in INSTALLED_APPS in settings

## Database Rules
- PostgreSQL only
- Always define __str__ method on every model
- Always define Meta class with verbose_name and verbose_name_plural
- Use select_related and prefetch_related to avoid N+1 queries
- Never use raw SQL unless absolutely necessary

## Business Rules from PCS Document
- Root Admin (first superuser) can never be suspended or have role changed
- Admin status values: Pending_Activation, Active, Suspended only
- Passwords are never set by Super Admin — invite link flow only (Phase 2)
- All audit-sensitive actions must be logged (Phase 10)

## Phase 1 — Roles & Admin Users Business Rules

### Roles Master Rules (FRM-CP-01-02)
- role_id must be UUID primary key
- role_name_en must be UNIQUE
- role_name_ar must be UNIQUE
- status values: Active, Inactive ONLY
- is_system_default = True means: cannot be deleted, cannot be set to Inactive, core properties cannot be modified
- A Role cannot be deleted if any active AdminUser is assigned to it — set Inactive instead
- Roles with is_system_default = True are seeded automatically — never created from UI
- Only Active roles appear in AdminUser creation dropdown
- created_by and updated_by must always be set to the currently logged-in admin

### Admin Users Master Rules (FRM-CP-01-01)
- admin_id must be UUID primary key
- email must be UNIQUE across entire control panel DB
- status values: Pending_Activation, Active, Suspended ONLY
- Default status on creation: Pending_Activation
- Super Admin never sets password — invite link flow handles it
- Root Admin (is_root = True) can NEVER be suspended
- Root Admin role can NEVER be changed
- Changing status to Suspended must immediately invalidate that user's session
- two_factor_enabled is read-only flag — only changed by auth system
- last_login_at is read-only — only updated by login system
- created_by and updated_by must always be set

### General Rules
- No hard delete on any record — use status changes only
- All list pages must have search, filter, and pagination
- All forms must show validation errors inline
- All sensitive actions (create, update, suspend) must be restricted to is_root = True users only in Phase 1

## Phase 2 — Full Auth Hardening Business Rules

### Admin Security Settings Rules (FRM-CP-11-01)
- Only ONE record ever exists in DB — fixed ID: "ADMIN-SEC-CONF"
- session_timeout_minutes: default 240 (4 hours)
- max_failed_logins: default 3
- lockout_duration_minutes: default 30
- updated_by must always be set to currently logged-in admin
- These values are read dynamically by auth system — never hardcoded

### Brute Force Protection Rules
- Failed attempts tracked per email in DB
- Counter increments on every failed login
- When counter reaches max_failed_logins → status becomes Blocked
- Blocked accounts cannot login until lockout_duration_minutes passes
- Successful login resets failed attempt counter to 0
- Lockout expiry is calculated: locked_at + lockout_duration_minutes
- Show remaining lockout time on login page

### Session Security Rules
- Session expiry is read from AdminSecuritySettings.session_timeout_minutes
- Every request checks if session is still valid
- If expired → clear session → redirect to login with message
- Session last activity timestamp updated on every request
- Middleware handles this — not views

### Invite Token Rules
- Token generated using Django secrets.token_urlsafe(32)
- Token stored in DB with created_at and expires_at (24 hours)
- Token is single-use — mark as used after password set
- Expired tokens show error page — cannot be reused
- Invalid tokens show error page
- In Phase 2: link is displayed on screen — no email sent yet
- TODO comment added everywhere email should be sent in Phase 7

### Password Reset Token Rules
- Same token mechanism as invite
- Expiry: 1 hour (shorter than invite)
- Single use only
- Only works for Active or Pending_Activation accounts
- Suspended accounts cannot reset password

### Access Log Rules (FRM-CP-11-04)
- Strictly append-only — no update, no delete ever
- Records: Login, Logout, Token_Refresh attempt types
- Records: Success, Failed, Blocked statuses
- Always captures email_used even if user does not exist
- Always captures IP address
- Always captures timestamp
- User domain: Admin only in Phase 2

## Phase 3 — Global Master Data Business Rules

### Countries Master Rules (FRM-CP-08-01)
- country_code is Primary Key — ISO format (e.g., SA, US, AE) — UPPERCASE only
- country_code is IMMUTABLE once saved — never allow edit of PK
- name_en: required, unique
- name_ar: required, unique
- is_active: default True
- NO hard delete ever — only deactivate (is_active = False)
- created_by: FK to AdminUser, set on creation only
- updated_at: auto timestamp on every save
- No created_at field — updated_at serves as audit timestamp
- Only active countries appear in any dropdown across the system
- Phase 3 note: Redis caching is deferred — add TODO comment where
  cache invalidation should happen when Redis is implemented in Phase 10

### Currencies Master Rules (FRM-CP-08-02)
- currency_code is Primary Key — ISO format (e.g., SAR, USD) — UPPERCASE only
- currency_code is IMMUTABLE once saved — block edit of PK at view level
- name_en: required
- name_ar: required
- currency_symbol: required (e.g., $, ريال)
- decimal_places: optional, default 2
- is_active: default True
- NO hard delete ever — only deactivate
- created_by: FK to AdminUser, set on creation only
- updated_at: auto timestamp
- Only active currencies appear in Subscription Plans, 
  Payment Methods, and any financial dropdowns
- currency_code immutability enforced in form clean() method —
  if editing and currency_code changed → raise ValidationError

### Seeding Rules
- Phase 3 seed must include common countries and currencies
- Saudi Arabia (SA) and USD/SAR must always be seeded
- Seed is idempotent — get_or_create pattern always
- seed_superadmin.py must be updated with seed_countries() 
  and seed_currencies() functions

## Phase 4 — System Configurations & Tax Business Rules

### Tax Codes Master Rules (FRM-CP-09-01)
- tax_code is Primary Key — unique (e.g., S-15, Z-0)
- tax_code is IMMUTABLE once saved — disable on edit
- rate_percent: Decimal, 0.00 to 100.00 only
- applicable_country_code: FK to Country, optional (null=True)
- is_default_for_country: only ONE tax code can be True
  per applicable_country_code — enforce in clean()
- is_international_default: only ONE record globally can be True
  — enforce in clean()
- Both is_default_for_country and is_international_default
  cannot both be True on same record
- is_active: default True
- No hard delete — deactivate only
- created_by, updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps

### General Tax Settings Rules (FRM-CP-09-02)
- Only ONE record ever — fixed ID: "GLOBAL-TAX-SETTING"
- prices_include_tax: Boolean, default False
- location_verification: ENUM choices:
    Profile_Only, Audit_Only, Enforce_Profile_Match
- updated_by must always be set on save

### IRoad Legal Identity Rules (FRM-CP-09-03)
- Only ONE record ever — fixed ID: "GLOBAL-LEGAL-IDENTITY"
- company_logo: image file upload — store in media/legal/
- company_country_code: FK to Country (required)
- commercial_register: required, numeric format
- tax_number: required
- support_email: required, valid email
- updated_by must always be set on save

### Global System Rules (FRM-CP-09-04)
- Only ONE record ever — fixed ID: "GLOBAL-SYSTEM-RULES"
- system_timezone: valid Python timezone string
- default_date_format: ENUM — YYYY-MM-DD or DD/MM/YYYY
- grace_period_days: Integer, minimum 0
- standard_billing_cycle: Integer, default 30, minimum 1
- updated_by must always be set on save

### Base Currency Rules (FRM-CP-09-05)
- Only ONE record ever — fixed ID: "GLOBAL-BASE-CURRENCY"
- base_currency_id: FK to Currency (required)
- IMMUTABILITY RULE: Once set AND first financial transaction
  exists (Phase 5), base_currency_id becomes read-only
  In Phase 4: allow setting but show strong warning on change
  Add TODO: # TODO Phase 5: Block change if transactions exist
- updated_by must always be set on save

### FX Exchange Rate Rules (FRM-CP-09-06)
- fx_id: UUID primary key
- currency_id: FK to Currency — must be Active currency
- currency_id CANNOT be the Base Currency
- exchange_rate: Decimal 10,6 precision — must be > 0
- is_active: default True
- Only ONE active FX rate record per currency allowed
- updated_by must always be set on save

### FX Rate Change Log Rules (FRM-CP-09-07)
- log_id: UUID primary key
- Strictly append-only — no update, no delete ever
- Auto-created by backend when FX rate is saved/updated
- Admin cannot manually create entries from UI
- changed_by: FK to AdminUser (who made the change)
- changed_at: auto timestamp
- Override save() to block updates (same pattern as AccessLog)
- Override delete() to block deletion

## Phase 5 — Subscription Plans Business Rules

### Subscription Plans Master Rules (FRM-CP-02-01)
- plan_id: UUID primary key
- plan_name_en: required, unique
- plan_name_ar: required, unique
- base_cycle_days: Integer, default 30, minimum 1
- is_active: default True
  If False, plan hidden from new subscriptions
- Resource limits: max_internal_users, max_internal_trucks,
  max_external_trucks, max_active_drivers,
  max_monthly_shipments, max_storage_gb
  All are IntegerField — entering -1 means Unlimited
  UI must show "Unlimited" checkbox that sets value to -1
- has_driver_app: Boolean default False
- backup_restore_level: ENUM — Standard, Extended, Premium
  default Standard
- created_by: FK to AdminUser, set on creation only
- created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps
- No hard delete — deactivate only
- A plan with active tenant subscriptions cannot be deactivated
  Add TODO: # TODO Phase 6: Check active subscribers before
  #          deactivating a plan

### Plan Pricing Cycles Rules (Subform)
- pricing_id: UUID primary key
- plan_id: FK to SubscriptionPlan (required)
- number_of_cycles: Integer, minimum 1
- currency_code: FK to Currency (active only)
- price: Decimal 10,2 minimum 0.00
- Combination of plan_id + number_of_cycles + currency_code
  must be UNIQUE — no duplicate pricing rows
- At least ONE pricing row required before plan is usable
- Deleting a pricing row is allowed only if plan has no
  active subscribers on that cycle

### Global Add-ons Pricing Policy Rules (FRM-CP-02-02)
- policy_id: UUID primary key
- policy_name: required, max 50 chars
- is_active: default False
- SINGULARITY RULE: When is_active set to True,
  all other policy records must be set to False automatically
- Only ONE active policy at any time
- All price fields: Decimal 10,2 minimum 0.00
- updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- updated_at: auto timestamp
- No hard delete — deactivate only

### Promo Codes Master Rules (FRM-CP-02-03)
- promo_code_id: UUID primary key
- code: required, UNIQUE, max 20 chars,
  alphanumeric only, auto-UPPERCASE
- discount_type: ENUM — Percentage, Fixed_Amount
- discount_value: Decimal 10,2
  If Percentage: max value is 100.00
  If Fixed_Amount: must be > 0
- discount_duration: ENUM — Apply_Once, Recurring
- valid_from: required, default now
- valid_until: optional, null allowed
  If set: must be after valid_from
- max_uses: optional, null means unlimited
  If set: must be >= 1
- current_uses: Integer default 0, read-only
  Only system increments this on successful payment
- is_active: Boolean default True
- applicable_plans: ManyToMany to SubscriptionPlan
  Empty = applies to ALL plans
- created_by: FK to AdminUser
- created_at: auto timestamp
- Validation order when applying to order:
  1. is_active check
  2. valid_from/until check
  3. max_uses > current_uses check
  4. applicable_plans check
  If any fails: raise "Invalid or Expired Code" error

## Phase 6 — Payment Infrastructure Business Rules

### Bank Accounts Master Rules (FRM-CP-07-01)
- account_id: UUID primary key
- bank_name: required, max 100 chars
- account_holder_name: required, max 100 chars
- iban_number: required, must pass IBAN format validation
  IBAN format: starts with 2 uppercase letters (country code)
  followed by 2 digits then up to 30 alphanumeric chars
  Total length: 15 to 34 chars
  Store in UPPERCASE, strip spaces before saving
- account_number: required, numeric only
- swift_code: optional, max 11 chars,
  format: 8 or 11 alphanumeric chars uppercase
- currency_code: FK to Currency (active only, required)
  Determines which orders can use this bank account
- is_active: default True
  If False, hidden from tenant checkout
- created_by, updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps
- No hard delete — deactivate only

### Payment Gateway API Rules (FRM-CP-07-02)
- gateway_id: UUID primary key
- gateway_name: required, max 50 chars
- environment: ENUM — Test, Live
- credentials_payload: JSONField — required
  Must be valid JSON object (not array, not null)
  Keys and values stored as-is — backend extracts what it needs
  Display masked in UI — never show raw values after save
- is_active: default False (must explicitly activate)
- No singularity rule — multiple gateways can be active
  (different gateways for different methods)
- created_by, updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps
- No hard delete — deactivate only

### Payment Methods Configuration Rules (FRM-CP-07-03)
- method_id: UUID primary key
- method_name_en: required, max 100 chars
- method_name_ar: required, max 100 chars
- method_type: ENUM — Online_Gateway, Offline_Bank
- supported_currencies: JSONField — array of currency codes
  e.g. ["SAR", "USD"]
  Must be valid JSON array
  Each code must exist in active Currency master
  Minimum 1 currency required
- gateway_id: FK to PaymentGateway
  REQUIRED if method_type = Online_Gateway
  Must be null if method_type = Offline_Bank
- dedicated_bank_account_id: FK to BankAccount
  Optional — only relevant if method_type = Offline_Bank
  Must be null if method_type = Online_Gateway
- logo_url: ImageField upload_to='payment_methods/'
  Optional
- display_order: IntegerField default=1, min 1
  Controls sort order in checkout UI
- is_active: default True
- created_by, updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps
- No hard delete — deactivate only

### Checkout Router Logic (to implement in Phase 8)
- Fetch methods where is_active=True AND
  order currency in supported_currencies array
- Add TODO comments in views where this logic will be used

## Phase 7 — Communication & Alerts Business Rules

### Communication Gateways Rules (FRM-CP-05-01)
- gateway_id: UUID primary key
- gateway_type: ENUM — Email, SMS only
- provider_name: required, max 100 chars
- host_url: required (SMTP host or SMS API base URL)
- port: optional Integer (mainly for SMTP: 587, 465)
- username_key: required (SMTP username or SMS API key)
- password_secret: required — NEVER display after save
  Store as-is — encryption handled at infrastructure level
  Show masked input on form
- sender_id: required (From email OR SMS sender name)
- encryption_type: ENUM optional — TLS, SSL, None
- is_active: default False
- SINGULARITY RULE: Only ONE gateway per gateway_type
  can be active at any time
  When activating one → auto-deactivate all others
  of same gateway_type
- updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- No created_at — only updated_at (settings record)
- Test Connection button: Phase 7 shows button with
  TODO comment — actual SMTP/SMS dispatch in Phase 11
  Add: # TODO Phase 11: Implement actual test connection
  #               using stored credentials here

### Notification Templates Rules (FRM-CP-05-02)
- template_id: UUID primary key
- template_name: required, unique, max 100 chars
- channel_type: ENUM — Email, SMS
- category: ENUM — Transactional, Promotional
- subject_en: required ONLY if channel_type = Email
- subject_ar: required ONLY if channel_type = Email
- body_en: required always — supports {{variables}}
- body_ar: required always — supports {{variables}}
- is_active: default True
- created_by: FK to AdminUser
- No hard delete — deactivate only
- Available variables list hardcoded:
  {{client_name}}, {{otp_code}}, {{invoice_amount}},
  {{invoice_number}}, {{plan_name}}, {{expiry_date}},
  {{company_name}}, {{support_email}}

### Events Mapping Engine Rules (FRM-CP-05-03)
- mapping_id: UUID primary key
- system_event: ENUM — hardcoded list, never dynamic:
  OTP_Requested, Password_Changed, Invoice_Paid,
  Subscription_Activated, Subscription_Expired,
  Subscription_Renewed, Account_Suspended,
  Welcome_Email, Password_Reset_Requested,
  Payment_Failed, Support_Ticket_Created,
  Support_Ticket_Replied
- primary_channel: ENUM — Email, SMS
- primary_template_id: FK to NotificationTemplate
  filtered by primary_channel type
- fallback_channel: ENUM optional — Email, SMS
  Cannot be same as primary_channel
- fallback_template_id: FK to NotificationTemplate
  Required if fallback_channel is set
  Filtered by fallback_channel type
- is_active: default True
- updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- ONE mapping per system_event only
  (unique constraint on system_event)

### Push Notifications Rules (FRM-CP-05-04)
- notification_id: UUID primary key
- trigger_mode: ENUM — Manual_Broadcast, System_Event
- linked_event: ENUM (same hardcoded list as above)
  Required if trigger_mode = System_Event
  Hidden if trigger_mode = Manual_Broadcast
- target_audience: ENUM — All, Tenants, Drivers, Specific
  Required if trigger_mode = Manual_Broadcast
  Hidden if trigger_mode = System_Event
- specific_target_id: optional text FK reference
  Required if target_audience = Specific
- dispatch_status: ENUM — Draft, Scheduled, Completed
  Only for Manual_Broadcast — hidden for System_Event
- is_active: Boolean
  Only relevant for System_Event — hidden for Manual_Broadcast
- scheduled_at: optional DateTime
  Only for Manual_Broadcast
- created_by: FK to AdminUser

### System Banners Rules (FRM-CP-05-05)
- banner_id: UUID primary key
- severity: ENUM — Info, Warning, Critical
  Info=Blue, Warning=Yellow, Critical=Red
- is_dismissible: Boolean default True
- valid_from: required DateTime default now
- valid_until: optional DateTime
  If set: must be after valid_from
- is_active: Boolean default True
- Auto-hide logic: banner is considered expired if
  valid_until is set and current time > valid_until
  Show "Expired" badge in admin list

### Internal Alerts Routing Rules (FRM-CP-05-06)
- route_id: UUID primary key
- trigger_event: ENUM hardcoded list:
  New_Tenant_Registered, High_Priority_Ticket,
  Payment_Failed, Subscription_Expired,
  Bank_Transfer_Pending, System_Error
- notify_role_id: FK to Role (optional)
  If set: all admins with this role get notified
- notify_custom_email: optional email field
  At least ONE of notify_role_id or
  notify_custom_email must be provided
- is_active: default True

### Communication Logs Rules (FRM-CP-05-07)
- log_id: UUID primary key
- Strictly append-only — override save() and delete()
  same pattern as AccessLog
- client_id: optional text field (not FK — tenant may
  not exist in this DB yet in Phase 7)
- channel_type: ENUM — Email, SMS, Push
- delivery_status: ENUM — Sent, Failed, Bounced
- dispatched_at: auto timestamp
- Retention: add TODO comment for 90-day archival
  # TODO Phase 11: Implement 90-day log archival/cleanup


## Phase 8 — Subscribers CRM & Billing Business Rules

### Tenant Profile Rules (FRM-CP-04-01)
- tenant_id: UUID primary key
- Synced fields (read-only in admin UI):
  company_name, registration_number, tax_number,
  primary_email, primary_phone, country_code
  These are NEVER edited from CP — only synced via webhook
  Add TODO: # TODO Phase 12: Implement webhook sync here
- account_status: ENUM — Active, Suspended_Billing,
  Suspended_Violation, Churned
  Default: Active
- KILL SWITCH: Changing to any Suspended state must:
  1. Save the status change
  2. Add TODO: # TODO Phase 10: Revoke all tenant
  #             JWT tokens via Redis Kill Switch here
- assigned_sales_rep: FK to AdminUser (optional)
  Only show Active admin users in dropdown
- wallet_balance: Decimal read-only
  Auto-calculated from transactions ledger
- registered_at: auto timestamp — read-only
- total_ltv: Decimal read-only
  Sum of all Paid invoices for this tenant
- Subscription state fields (all read-only — auto-updated
  when order_status becomes Paid):
  current_plan_id, subscription_start_date,
  subscription_expiry_date, active_max_users,
  active_max_internal_trucks, active_max_external_trucks,
  active_max_drivers
- updated_at: auto timestamp
- No hard delete of tenant profiles ever

### CRM Notes Rules (FRM-CP-04-02)
- note_id: UUID primary key
- Strictly immutable — no edit, no delete ever
- Override save() to block updates
- Override delete() to block deletion
- note_type: ENUM — General, Sales_Call,
  Billing_Issue, Complaint
- note_content: required TextField
- admin_id: FK to AdminUser (who wrote it)
- created_at: auto timestamp

### Subscription Order Rules (FRM-CP-04-03)
- order_id: UUID primary key
- order_classification: ENUM — New_Subscription,
  Renewal, Upgrade, Downgrade, Add_ons
- order_status: ENUM — Draft, Pending_Payment,
  Paid, Cancelled
  Default: Draft
- PROVISIONING RULE: Tenant limits and dates ONLY
  updated when order_status transitions to Paid
- tax_id: FK to TaxCode — auto-fetched based on
  tenant country at order creation
- exchange_rate_snapshot: Decimal 10,6
  Snapshot of FX rate at order creation time
  Never changes after creation
- Projected fields: all read-only, recalculated on
  each order save based on classification logic
- promo_code: FK to PromoCode optional
  Validate using PromoCode.is_valid_for_use()
  before applying discount
- payment_method: FK to PaymentMethod optional
- created_by: FK to AdminUser

### Order Line Rules (Subform 1 — Plan)
- One row max per order
- plan: FK to SubscriptionPlan
- number_of_cycles: from plan pricing cycles
- plan_price: auto-fetched from PlanPricingCycle
- pro_rata_adjustment: calculated for Upgrade only
- line_total: plan_price + pro_rata_adjustment

### Order Line Rules (Subform 2 — Add-ons)
- Multiple rows allowed
- add_on_type: ENUM — Extra_User,
  Extra_Internal_Truck, Extra_External_Truck,
  Extra_Driver, Extra_Shipment, Extra_Storage_GB
- unit_price: auto-fetched from active AddOnsPricingPolicy
- number_of_cycles: fraction of remaining days for
  co-terming calculation
- line_total: quantity * unit_price * number_of_cycles

### Pro-Rata Calculation Rules (Hardcoded)
- Upgrade credit = (days_remaining / base_cycle_days)
    * current_plan_price
- Add-on daily rate = add_on_cycle_price / base_cycle_days
- Add-on charge = daily_rate * days_remaining_in_cycle
- Downgrade: no credit, deferred to expiry

### Transaction Ledger Rules (FRM-CP-04-04)
- transaction_id: UUID primary key
- transaction_type: ENUM — Order_Payment,
  Wallet_TopUp, Refund
- status: ENUM — Pending, Completed, Failed, Rejected
  Default: Pending
- exchange_rate_snapshot: Decimal 10,6
  Snapshot at transaction creation time
- base_currency_equivalent: amount * exchange_rate_snapshot
- attachment_url: FileField
  REQUIRED if payment_method is Offline_Bank type
- reviewed_by: FK to AdminUser read-only
  Set when admin approves or rejects
- review_notes: required when rejecting
- Bank Transfer Approval Flow:
  Approve → status=Completed → linked order status=Paid
            → generate Standard Invoice
            → update tenant subscription limits
  Reject → status=Rejected → review_notes required
           → order remains Pending_Payment

### Standard Invoice Rules (FRM-CP-04-05)
- invoice_id: UUID primary key
- invoice_number: auto-sequential INV-YYYY-NNNN
- ABSOLUTE IMMUTABILITY: once generated NO field
  can be modified
- Override save() to block any update after creation
- Override delete() to block deletion
- Voiding: status can change to Void ONLY
  Never delete — create Credit Note instead
- Snapshotting: supplier_name, supplier_tax_number,
  customer_name, customer_tax_number, customer_address
  ALL hard-copied at invoice generation time
- Generation trigger: auto-created when order
  status transitions to Paid
- invoice_number format: INV-{YEAR}-{4_digit_sequence}
  e.g. INV-2026-0001

## Phase 9 — Support Management Business Rules

### Support Categories Rules (FRM-CP-10-01)
- category_id: UUID primary key
- name_en: required, unique
- name_ar: required, unique
- is_active: default True
- No hard delete — deactivate only
- If deactivated: disappears from Tenant dropdown
- created_by: FK to AdminUser
- created_at, updated_at: auto timestamps

### Canned Responses Rules (FRM-CP-10-02)
- template_id: UUID primary key
- title: required, unique, max 100 chars (internal use)
- message_body: required LongText
- is_active: default True
- No hard delete — deactivate only
- Admin use only — never exposed to Tenant API

### Support Ticket Master Rules (FRM-CP-10-03)
- ticket_id: UUID primary key
- ticket_no: auto-sequential TKT-XXXXX (e.g. TKT-10001)
  format: TKT- + 5 digit zero-padded sequence
- tenant_id: FK to TenantProfile (required)
- subject: required, max 255 chars
- category_id: FK to SupportCategory (required)
- priority: ENUM — Low, Medium, High, Critical
  default: Medium
- status: ENUM — New, In_Progress, Pending_Client, Closed
  default: New
- assigned_to: FK to AdminUser — null allowed
  INVISIBLE to Tenant API
- created_by: CharField (Tenant User ID who opened it)
- created_at: auto timestamp
- closed_at: DateTimeField null — auto-set when
  status becomes Closed

### Auto State Machine Rules (Ping-Pong Logic)
- Trigger 1: New ticket created → status = New
- Trigger 2: assigned_to is set → status = In_Progress
- Trigger 3: Admin adds reply (is_internal=False)
  → status = Pending_Client
- Trigger 4: Tenant adds reply on open ticket
  → status = In_Progress
- Status transitions enforced in view logic — not in model

### Ticket Reply Rules (FRM-CP-10-04)
- reply_id: UUID primary key
- ticket_id: FK to SupportTicket (required)
- sender_type: ENUM — Tenant_User, Admin_Support,
  System_Bot
- sender_id: CharField (ID of sender)
- message_body: LongTextField required
- attachment: FileField null allowed
  upload_to='support_attachments/'
- is_internal: BooleanField default False
  If True: NEVER returned in Tenant-facing API
  NEVER visible to Tenant in any view
- created_at: auto timestamp (determines sort order)
- Immutable after creation — no edit allowed
  Override save() to block updates
  Override delete() to block deletion

### Tenant API Bridge Rules
- GET /api/v1/support/tickets/ — tenant sees only
  their own tickets (filter by tenant_id from JWT)
- GET /api/v1/support/tickets/<id>/ — detail view
  excludes is_internal=True replies
- POST /api/v1/support/tickets/ — tenant creates ticket
- POST /api/v1/support/tickets/<id>/reply/ — tenant replies
  Blocked if ticket status == Closed
- Tenant CANNOT: see assigned_to, see internal notes,
  change priority after creation, change status to Closed

### RBAC Rules
- Admin: sees all tickets, all replies including internal
- Admin: can change priority, assigned_to, force close
- Tenant: limited API access only — no CP access

## Phase 10 — Security & Audit Business Rules

### Admin Security Settings Rules (FRM-CP-11-01)
- Already exists from Phase 2 — do NOT recreate
- setting_id: fixed "ADMIN-SEC-CONF"
- session_timeout_minutes: default 240
- max_failed_logins: default 3
- lockout_duration_minutes: default 30
- updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- updated_at: auto timestamp
- Only ONE record ever

### Tenant Security Settings Rules (FRM-CP-11-02)
- setting_id: fixed "TENANT-SEC-CONF"
- Only ONE record ever — get_or_create pattern
- tenant_web_timeout_hours: Integer default 12
- driver_app_timeout_days: Integer default 30
- max_failed_logins: Integer default 5
- lockout_duration_minutes: Integer default 15
- updated_by: FK to AdminUser
- updated_at: auto timestamp

### Active Sessions Monitor Rules (FRM-CP-11-03)
- Sessions stored in Django DB (not Redis in Phase 10)
- Redis Kill Switch deferred to future phase
- Add TODO: # TODO Phase 11 Redis: Replace DB session
  #         store with Redis cache for real-time JWT
  #         revocation when Redis is implemented
- session_id: UUID primary key
- user_domain: ENUM — Admin, Tenant_User, Driver
- reference_id: CharField (user/driver ID)
- reference_name: CharField (display name for UI)
- ip_address: CharField
- user_agent: TextField
- started_at: DateTimeField auto_now_add
- is_active: BooleanField default True
- revoked_at: DateTimeField null — set when revoked
- revoked_by: FK to AdminUser null — who revoked it

### Session Revocation Rules
- Targeted Revocation: set is_active=False on one session
- Mass Revoke (Kill Switch): set is_active=False on ALL
  sessions where reference_id belongs to a Tenant
  Add TODO: # TODO Phase 11 Redis: When Redis is live,
  #         destroy actual JWT tokens here in addition
  #         to DB flag
- Sessions created automatically on login
  (hook into existing LoginView)
- Sessions marked inactive on logout

### Access Log Rules (FRM-CP-11-04)
- Already exists from Phase 2 as AccessLog model
- Do NOT recreate — just build the read-only view
- Confirm existing fields match FRM-CP-11-04:
  attempt_type, status, user_domain,
  email_used, ip_address, timestamp
- Strictly append-only — already enforced

### Master System Audit Log Rules (FRM-CP-11-05)
- audit_id: AutoField primary key (not UUID)
- admin: FK to AdminUser (required)
- action_type: ENUM — Create, Update, Delete,
  Status_Change
- module_name: CharField max 100
  e.g. "Tax Settings", "Subscription Plans"
- record_id: CharField max 100 (ID of modified entity)
- old_payload: JSONField null=True
  Null if action_type = Create
- new_payload: JSONField null=True
  Null if action_type = Delete
- ip_address: CharField max 45
- timestamp: DateTimeField auto_now_add=True
- Strictly append-only:
  Override save() to block updates
  Override delete() to block deletion
- No admin can modify or delete entries ever
- Helper function: log_audit_action() utility
  that other views call to record changes

## Phase 11 — Super Admin Dashboard Business Rules

### Dashboard Data Sources
- ALL data is pulled live from existing Phase 3–10 models
- NO hardcoded dummy data anywhere in views
- Dashboard is the first page after login — must load fast
- Use Django ORM aggregations — no raw SQL

### Executive KPIs (Top Row)
- MRR (Monthly Recurring Revenue):
  Sum of grand_total from StandardInvoice where
  status='Issued' OR status='Paid'
  AND issue_date within current calendar month
  Display in Base Currency (SAR)
- Active Tenants:
  Count of TenantProfile where account_status='Active'
- Pending Orders:
  Count of SubscriptionOrder where order_status='Pending_Payment'
- Failed / Pending Transactions:
  Count of Transaction where status='Pending'
  AND payment_method__method_type='Offline_Bank'
- Open Support Tickets:
  Count of SupportTicket where status in ['New','In_Progress']
- Overdue Tickets:
  Count of SupportTicket where status not in ['Closed']
  AND created_at < now() - 48 hours
- Active Admin Sessions:
  Count of ActiveSession where is_active=True
  AND user_domain='Admin'

### Attention Center (Action Items)
- Pending Bank Transfer Orders: list top 5
  SubscriptionOrder where order_status='Pending_Payment'
  order by created_at ascending (oldest first)
- Overdue Support Tickets: list top 5
  SupportTicket where status != 'Closed'
  AND created_at < now() - 48 hours
  order by created_at ascending
- Failed Transactions: list top 5
  Transaction where status in ['Failed','Rejected']
  order by created_at descending
- Recently Suspended Tenants: list top 5
  TenantProfile where account_status != 'Active'
  order by updated_at descending

### Staff Analytics Section
- Role Distribution: Count of AdminUser grouped by role
- Stale Accounts: AdminUser where last_login_at < 30 days ago
  OR last_login_at is null
- Active Admin Sessions count live from ActiveSession model
- Suspended Admin Accounts: count where status='Suspended'

### Revenue Chart
- Last 6 months bar chart
  Group StandardInvoice by month
  Sum grand_total per month (base currency equivalent)
- Data from base_currency_equivalent_amount field

### Recent Activity Feed
- Last 10 AuditLog entries
  Show: admin name, action_type, module_name, timestamp

## Phase 12 — Unified UI Template System Rules

### Golden Rules (NEVER violate)
- NEVER change any Python view logic
- NEVER change any URL pattern
- NEVER change any model or form
- NEVER remove any permission check (is_root, LoginRequired)
- NEVER remove any feature (search, filter, toggle, delete)
- NEVER change any Django template tag that calls a URL
- NEVER change API structure or JSON responses
- ONLY refactor the HTML/CSS structure to match unified templates
- ALL business logic stays 100% identical

### Unified List Page Rules
- Every list template must follow Client-account.html structure
- Must have: page toolbar (title + subtitle + action button)
- Must have: search bar + filter dropdowns in one row
- Must have: results count badge ("Showing X of Y")
- Must have: data table with consistent column styling
- Must have: status badge column (Active=green, Inactive=gray,
  other statuses use correct colors per module)
- Must have: actions column (Edit, Toggle, View as applicable)
- Must have: delete confirmation modal (same structure always)
- Must have: pagination block at bottom
- Must have: empty state card when no results
- Table header: sticky, slightly darker background
- Table rows: hover highlight, alternating subtle background

### Unified Create/Edit Page Rules
- Every form template must follow Client-account-new.html structure
- Must have: page toolbar with breadcrumb
  (Module List > Create / Module List > Edit: Record Name)
- Must have: form card with section headers for grouped fields
- Must have: consistent label + input layout (label above input)
- Must have: inline validation error display below each field
- Must have: sticky footer action bar:
    Left: Cancel button (links back to list)
    Right: Save button (primary color)
- Edit mode: show "last updated by + timestamp" info banner
- Read-only fields: shown as disabled inputs with lock icon
- Immutable fields (PKs on edit): shown with info alert at top

### Delete Confirmation Modal Rules
- Triggered by delete button click
- Shows record name in modal body
- Two buttons: Cancel (gray) + Confirm Delete (red)
- On confirm: POST to delete URL
- Error state: if delete blocked, show error in same modal

### Consistency Rules
- All page titles follow format: "Module Name" (no "Master" suffix in H1)
- All subtitles: one-line description of what the page manages
- All search inputs: same placeholder format "Search by name, code..."
- All filter dropdowns: same size and alignment
- All action buttons: same size, icons from Bootstrap Icons only
- All status badges: pill shape, consistent padding
- Empty states: always show relevant icon + message + CTA button


## Redis + Celery Full Implementation Rules


### Redis Session Rules

- ALL admin sessions stored in Redis — NOT Django DB sessions

- Redis key pattern for admin sessions:

    admin:session:{jti}

    Value: JSON with admin_id, email, ip_address, 

           user_agent, started_at, last_activity

    TTL: session_timeout_minutes * 60 (in seconds)

- On every authenticated request: refresh TTL in Redis

- On logout: delete Redis key immediately

- On suspend: delete ALL Redis keys for that admin

- Session ID (JTI) stored in Django session only as reference pointer

- Never store password or sensitive tokens in Redis


### JWT Rules

- Use PyJWT for token generation

- JWT payload must contain: jti, admin_id, email, issued_at

- jti (JWT ID) is uuid4 — unique per session

- JWT secret loaded from .env SECRET_KEY

- JWT used only for session identification — not for API auth yet


### Celery Rules

- Broker: Redis DB 1

- Result Backend: Redis DB 2

- All tasks defined in superadmin/tasks.py

- All tasks must be idempotent — safe to retry

- All tasks wrapped in try/except with proper logging

- Task naming: iroad.{module}.{action}

  e.g., iroad.auth.revoke_tenant_sessions

- Never call tasks synchronously — always .delay() or .apply_async()


### Kill Switch Rules (PCS P3 Rule B + P11)

- Suspending admin: delete their Redis session key immediately

- Suspending tenant: delete all Redis keys matching tenant pattern

  (Phase 8 — tenant keys not yet created but pattern reserved)

- Kill switch must be atomic — use Redis pipeline


### Active Sessions Monitor Rules (FRM-CP-11-03)

- Sessions read from Redis SCAN — not from DB

- Fields shown: session_id, user_domain, admin email,

  ip_address, user_agent, started_at, last_activity

- Revoke button: deletes Redis key immediately

- Data is live — no pagination cache


### Celery Task Rules

- Email task: reads active SMTP gateway from DB, sends via smtplib

- SMS task: reads active SMS gateway from DB, sends via HTTP

- Expiry task: runs daily via Celery Beat

- All tasks log result to Django logger

